This piece of advice goes into nearly every single review that I write. It's changed the way I write, and it has also mildly cursed me in the same way that [XKCD's comic on kerning](https://xkcd.com/1015/) did. Too many times I now see something like:

> "Figure 1. a heatmap of disease prevalance in <location>."

So perhaps it is a blessing and a curse to have this knowledge. But I think the blessing is worth it.

Thanks again to Di Cook for sharing this knowledge many years ago
